<br>
It is looking like the low level styles are losing around 100-150pts per style hit (example: live servers: Snowblind average for me is 250ish on 50 zerks; Pendragon against 50zerks its 140); the higher level styles are effected even more... snowsqual hasn't been able to break 300 even on sitting opponents, Icy brilliance and AB are unable to break 250.<br>
<br>
this is with a 50 zerk using MP cleaver/MP WBA, RR5 with 65 Left Axe, 59 Axe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=znailvh>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#000000>(4/23/03 1:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Prelimary testing on new patch</span><hr size=1> Test it against level 1 mobs instead. The capped damage shows clearly how large the change is. Testing against players looking at averages is a very unexact way to test it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kethryndc>Kethryn DC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#000000>(4/23/03 3:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Prelimary testing on new patch</span><hr size=1> Testing against players is the only way to test because it shows how it will work in RvR.<br>
<br>
And against level 1 mobs is very wrong.  They have a cap on how much damage they can take that is not related to your cap damage.  If you want to test caps on greys you have to test against one thats not going to die in one hit.<br>
<br>
*******<br>
<br>
Back to the testing results:<br>
<br>
Vs. Hammer using Warrior - Warrior - faster swing speed; same damage per hit<br>
<br>
Vs. 2-handed using Skald - Skald slightly slower swing speed and 50% more damage per hit.<br>
<br>
Savages are not only triple and quad hitting but doing same damage per hit much much quicker then Zerks.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=znailvh>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#000000>(4/23/03 7:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Prelimary testing on new patch</span><hr size=1> The damage caps against grey mobs are directly related to the damage you can do. If you do a style that gives you a 100% damage bonus, then the cap will be 200% of the cap for a unstyled hit etc... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kethryndc>Kethryn DC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#000000>(4/23/03 8:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Prelimary testing on new patch</span><hr size=1> What I'm saying is the &quot;cap&quot; you are hitting on level 1 mobs is not the cap for your style.  But a relationship between that style and the damage that the mob can take.<br>
<br>
Go smack a wildling... you'll get a number of damage.<br>
<br>
Go smack level 30 critter, you'll get a completly different number (much larger most of the time). <br>
<br>
The reason is that the level 1,2 ,5, etc critter has X hits.. it will only take X+some unknown number of damage. Everything above that is wasted and not related to the style being used. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=znailvh>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#000000>(4/23/03 10:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Prelimary testing on new patch</span><hr size=1> Kethryn, I suggest you do try this out. I have and what you are talking about is not happening. I think your theory about mob hits affecting max damage is faulty. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=avandor>Avandor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Axe-Wielding Maniac</span><br>  Posts: 470<br> <font color=#000000>(4/23/03 11:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.webinnovations.dk/av/albanim.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Prelimary testing on new patch</span><hr size=1> Grim, I think they are correct.<br>
